So, for soloing at 64 you're going to have the choice of a 52nd or 53rd (wih a focus item from VT) level pet with probably 4k+ hp and epic level damage output + a 33 (or 35) pt DS ----- OR ----- a 49th level pet with 4.3k hp and a 50pt DS, epic level (obviously) melee DPS and huge procs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uetadanikm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EtadanikM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 2:58:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1407.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Can't you just see the painless solution?</span><hr size=1> Epic 2, with a necessary turn-in of epic 1 at the end, would be the painless solution, pure and smiple.<br>
<br>
1. VI could make the new pets better than the epic, with the argument that no Kunark-era item should be better than power gained in PoP, and thus guaranteeing that PoP characters will be stronger than Luclin characters.<br>
<br>
2. People who already have the epic and spent the time necessary to obtain it won't feel slighted, because their time will not be wasted as epic 2 will require epic 1.  <br>
<br>
3. Epic 2 will ensure that mages will have a goal to strive towards, so that epic mages won't just get bored because none of their new pets can match the epic pet's power, so their power don't really increase as they level.<br>
<br>
This is the obvious solution, and in my mind the best one.  It is a great compromise between the upgrade-epic and epic-is-obsolete crowd, and therefore unlike the extremes it will to a degree be acceptable to both crowds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugnuu2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gnuu2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 11:57:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1407.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  epics</span><hr size=1> maybe verrant thought of this&quot;adding a focus&quot; to the pet,It looks like we can embulm gems now maybe getting these spells will be used for giving the epic all these elemental gems to make epic a power house once again? and if you give the pets thier gem fire to fire pet ect.. it will give them increased power as well? this way the old epic will still be around and you dont have to do another quest to get the upgraded pet. we all know what verrant does for mage epics.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugnuu2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gnuu2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 12:01:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1407.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  epics</span><hr size=1> never mind just looked up the gems again and the